properties.headline: Wind Chill Advisory issued January 18 at 7:57AM AKST until January 18 at 9:00PM AKST by NWS Anchorage, AK
properties.description:
* WHAT...Very cold wind chills. Wind chills 40 to 50 below zero.

* WHERE...Thompson Pass.

* WHEN...Until 9 PM AKST this evening.

* IMPACTS...The dangerously cold wind chills could cause
frostbite on exposed skin in as little as 10 minutes.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Winds will continue to gust as high as 50
mph through the day as temperatures slowly rise by tonight.
properties.instruction:
Use caution while traveling outside. Wear appropriate clothing, a
hat, and gloves.

NWSheadline: WIND CHILL ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL 9 PM AKST THIS EVENING THROUGH THOMPSON PASS
